questions.explanation:
Let: a _n = number of n-bit strings that do not have two consecutive 1’s.
If n=1, possible strings {0,1}
a _1 = 2
If n=2, possible strings {00,01,10}
a _2 = 3
If n=3,
possible strings {000,001,010,100,101}
a _3 = 5
It is evident that a _3 = a _ 1 + a _2
Similarly, a _n = a _n-1 + a _n-2

